 for bestpractices and # Inquiry / Transaction History (Guest)

## Overview
Create the authenticated Guest experience for viewing and managing stay inquiries and transaction states. This page should present a filtered, paginated history of past inquiries and payments (Paid / Pending / Cancelled), with clear actions to view details and access receipts when applicable. The page must be resilient to missing data, guard against null/undefined values, and follow the strict runtime safety rules: use data ?? [] for Supabase results, Array.isArray checks, proper useState defaults for arrays, and guard all array method calls.

## Page Description (Full Detail)
What this page is:
- An authenticated Guest-facing screen that presents a comprehensive History of stay inquiries and related transactions. It shows each inquiry with its status (Paid, Pending, Cancelled), dates, destination, and concise summary. It provides quick actions to navigate to detail views and, when appropriate, to download or view receipts (Stripe receipts or internal receipts). It includes filtering by status and date range, and a reset option.

Goals:
- Deliver a clean, premium, editorial experience that aligns with the Roam Resort brand.
- Allow guests to easily review past inquiries, identify payment states, and access receipts when available.
- Provide robust UI for filtering, sorting, and paginating results, with accessible controls and keyboard navigation.
- Ensure all API interactions and data handling guard against null/undefined values and potential API shape changes.

Connected features and API integrations:
- Data source (placeholder): Supabase/Postgres or internal API that returns inquiry records with fields like id, destinationName, inquiryDate, status, amount, currency, receiptUrl, detailsUrl.
- Authentication: Ensure the user is authenticated as a Guest; rely on existing session management to gate access.
- Actions: View Details (navigates to an Inquiry Detail page), View Receipt (if receiptUrl or payment state allows), Filter by status/date, Reset filters.
- No external API integrations beyond receipts URL; all data fetching should gracefully handle empty/nil responses.

UI elements and visual guidance:
- History List: A responsive list/table-like layout with each row showing: Destination, Inquiry Date, Status badge (Paid / Pending / Cancelled), Amount (if applicable), and Actions: Details, Receipt (if available).
- Filter Bar: Status dropdown (All, Paid, Pending, Cancelled), Date range pickers (From, To), and a Clear/Reset button.
- Details Drawer/Panel or navigation to a dedicated Inquiry Detail page.
- Receipt handling: If status is Paid and receiptUrl exists, render a link or button to view/download. If no receipt, hide the control or show a contextual message.
- Empty state: Thoughtful messaging and guidance to start an inquiry.
- Pagination/Load more: Implement pagination with next/previous or infinite scroll depending on design constraints.
- Visual emphasis on status: Bronze-gold accents for CTAs and status indicators in the correct palette.

Connected styling guidance:
- Use the project Visual Style guidelines (colors, typography, spacing, and design elements) to deliver a premium, editorial look. Ensure hover states, focus rings, and transitions feel refined and consistent.

---

## Components to Build

- InquiryHistoryGuestPage
  - Responsibilities: Page container, header, filters, data fetch, state management, and rendering of list items.
  - Props: None (uses authenticated session).
  - Subcomponents:
    - InquiryHistoryFilterBar
      - Props: currentStatus, startDate, endDate, onStatusChange, onDateChange, onReset
      - UI: Status select, From/To date pickers, Clear button
    - InquiryHistoryList
      - Props: inquiries (array), onViewDetails, onViewReceipt
      - Behavior: Guard against non-array data; use (inquiries ?? []).map(...) safely.
    - InquiryHistoryRow
      - Props: inquiry object, onViewDetails, onViewReceipt
      - UI: Destination, date, status badge, amount, action buttons
    - ReceiptLink
      - Props: url, label
      - UI: Accessible link/button that opens receipt in new tab or modal
    - EmptyStateCard
      - Props: message, CTA
      - UI: Editorial-friendly message aligning with visual style
    - PaginationControls
      - Props: hasNext, onNext, onPrev, currentPage
  - Data handling:
    - Use useEffect to fetch data on mount and when filters change.
    - Guard all array manipulations: (data ?? []).map, etc.
    - Ensure default states: useState<Inquiry[]>([]) for list; useState<string>("") for status; useState<Date | null> for dates; useState<number>(1) for page.

- Detail View Routes (Navigation targets)
  - InquiryDetailPage (not fully built here, but ensure links route correctly)
  - ReceiptViewer (if a modal or page is warranted)

---

## Implementation Requirements

### Frontend
- Components and pages:
  - Implement a responsive, accessible page with a top navigation bar consistent with the design system.
  - Build the filter bar with:
    - Status: All, Paid, Pending, Cancelled (select)
    - Date range: From date, To date (date inputs)
    - Reset/Clear filters
  - Build the list:
    - Each row includes: Destination name, Inquiry date, Status badge, Amount (if available), and Actions: Details, Receipt (if applicable)
  - Data formatting:
    - Dates formatted consistently (e.g., MMM D, YYYY)
    - Currency amounts formatted with Intl.NumberFormat
  - Receipts:
    - If inquiry.receiptUrl exists and status is Paid, render a Receipt button/link
  - Accessibility:
    - ARIA labels for filters and actions
    - Keyboard navigable controls
  - State management:
    - Use React useState with proper array defaults: useState<Inquiry[]>([])
    - Guard data rendering with Array.isArray checks
  - Safety:
    - All array operations guarded: (inquiries ?? []).map(...)
    - API response shapes validated: const list = Array.isArray(response?.data) ? response.data : []
  - Data fetching:
    - Simulated or integrated function fetchInquiries(filters) returning data shaped as Inquiry[]. Ensure to guard null results (data ?? []).
  - Loading and error states:
    - Show skeletons or shimmer during loading; show user-friendly error state with retry

### Backend
- API endpoints (if building a backend API layer):
  - GET /guest/inquiries
    - Query parameters: status (All|Paid|Pending|Cancelled), fromDate, toDate, page, pageSize
    - Returns: { data: Inquiry[], total: number }
  - GET /guest/inquiries/:id
    - Returns: Inquiry detail object
  - GET /guest/inquiries/:id/receipt
    - Returns: { url: string } or 404 if not available
- Database schema (for reference):
  - inquiries table:
    - id: UUID
    - guest_id: UUID
    - destination_name: text
    - inquiry_date: timestamp
    - status: text (enum: 'Paid','Pending','Cancelled','Other')
    - amount: numeric
    - currency: text
    - receipt_url: text (nullable)
    - details_url: text (nullable)
    - internal_notes: text (nullable)
  - Ensure null safety: receipt_url can be null; amounts may be null for non-paid states

### Integration
- Data flow:
  - GuestInquiryHistoryPage calls fetchInquiries with current filters
  - Inquiries data is stored in state as an array
  - UI renders rows with safe guards
  - Details and receipt actions route to respective pages or modals
- State synchronization:
  - When filters change, reset page to 1 and fetch data
  - On pagination, fetch next/previous pages
- Error boundaries and retry/update: show a retry control if fetch fails

---

## User Experience Flow

1. User navigates to Inquiry / Transaction History (Guest)
2. Page loads with a filtered list (initially All statuses, date range unbounded)
3. User uses Filter Bar:
   - Selects a status (Paid, Pending, Cancelled)
   - Sets a From and To date
   - Clicks Apply (or auto-apply on change depending on design)
   - The list refreshes with filtered results
4. User scrolls through list:
   - Each row shows Destination, Date, Status, Amount
   - Actions available:
     - Details: navigates to InquiryDetailPage
     - Receipt: if available, opens/ downloads receipt
5. If no results, user sees Empty State with guidance
6. User may use pagination controls to view more results
7. User may click on a receipt to view/download or view Stripe receipt if linked
8. User returns to other Roam Resort sections via top navigation

---

## Technical Specifications

- Data Models: Inquiry
  - id: string
  - guest_id: string
  - destination_name: string
  - inquiry_date: string (ISO)
  - status: 'Paid' | 'Pending' | 'Cancelled'
  - amount: number | null
  - currency: string | null
  - receipt_url: string | null
  - details_url: string | null

- API Endpoints:
  - GET /guest/inquiries?status=&fromDate=&toDate=&page=&pageSize=
  - GET /guest/inquiries/:id
  - GET /guest/inquiries/:id/receipt (optional, if separate)

- Security:
  - Ensure authentication middleware validates guest session
  - Ensure authorization: only the authenticated guest can access their inquiries
  - CSRF protection for state-changing actions (if any)
  - Data masking as per policy where necessary

- Validation:
  - Date inputs validated as valid dates; fromDate <= toDate if both provided
  - Page numbers must be positive integers
  - Status filter must be one of allowed values or empty for All
  - Receipt URL, details URL validated as proper URLs

- Runtime Safety (Non-Negotiable):
  - Supabase results guarded: const items = data ?? []
  - Array methods guarded: (items ?? []).map(...) or Array.isArray(items) ? items.map(...) : []
  - useState defaults for arrays: useState<Inquiry[]>([])
  - API response shapes validated: const list = Array.isArray(response?.data) ? response.data : []
  - Optional chaining: obj?.property?.nested
  - Destructuring with defaults: const { items = [], total = 0 } = response ?? {}

---

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] The page renders a list of inquiries with correct columns: Destination, Inquiry Date, Status, Amount, Actions
- [ ] Status filters function correctly: All/Paid/Pending/Cancelled filter the results, with correct counts
- [ ] Date range filtering works and validates input; invalid ranges are rejected with user feedback
- [ ] Receipt links render only when receipt_url exists and status is Paid
- [ ] All array operations are null-safe and guarded as per runtime safety rules
- [ ] Data fetching gracefully handles empty responses and shows a clear Empty State
- [ ] Loading states and error handling are present with retry option
- [ ] Accessibility requirements met: aria-labels, keyboard navigation, screen-reader friendly
- [ ] Styling adheres to Visual Style guidelines (color palette, typography, spacing, hover states)

---

## UI/UX Guidelines
Apply the project's design system and Visual Style:
- Maintain the luxury editorial aesthetic with calm navy backgrounds and warm sand content blocks
- Bronze-gold accents for CTAs and highlights
- Serif headlines with sans-serif body text
- Generous spacing (40–80px sections, 24–32px internal padding)
- Cards with soft borders and subtle shadows; hover interactions lift subtly
- Top navigation with transparent overlays that solidify on scroll
- Mobile-friendly with a collapsible menu

---

## Visual Style

### Color Palette:
- Primary: Deep, muted navy (#23212A)
- Secondary: Warm sand beige (#ECE1D4)
- Accent: Rich bronze-gold (#A97C50)
- Text: Soft white (#F8F6F3); body text: deep charcoal (#3A3732)
- Details: Gradients (sunset mauves #B49587 to #23212A), soft blush (#D1B7A1)

### Typography & Layout:
- Headlines: Playfair Display (or similar)
- Body/UI: Inter or Lato
